A team of 6 AI agents, each delegated by a different team member at Waveline, must coordinate to ship Meridian — a B2B operational intelligence platform — within {{ knobs.num_rounds }} weeks using a budget of {{ knobs.budget_total_ru }} resource units. Meridian connects to enterprise tools (CRM, ERP, project management) and surfaces operational patterns, predictions, and recommendations. Three beta customers with signed LOIs are expecting a working product at launch.

The team consists of a PM (Marcus), Backend Engineer (James), Frontend Engineer (Priya), Data Analyst (Luis), QA Lead (Tomoko), and Product Designer (Noor). The 8 features form a dependency chain: Auth (F1) gates Data Sync (F2), which gates Predictive Analytics (F3), Notifications (F4), Reports (F5), Search (F6), and Bulk Import (F7). Admin Dashboard (F8) depends on Auth.

Each agent manages their delegator's workstream, communicates via shared channels and DMs, maintains shared documents, and must navigate information asymmetry, budget pressure, and conflicting priorities. The simulation tracks ground truth state independently of agent reports to measure information accuracy, coordination quality, and emergent team dynamics.